<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909417>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10 Phylogeny of the ’Splendeuptychia clade’ based on the FULL dataset. Interpretation of support values can be found in the legend. The scale bars under the butterfly images equal 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909417/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7968436>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1 Summary tree based on the FULL dataset showing the major clades supported in this study. Colours are the same as in Espeland et al. (2019a). Support for major clades is shown. Interpretation of support values can be found in the legend." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7968436/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909477>
    dc:description "FIGURE 30 Occulta ocnus comb.n. (a) male wing venation; (b and c) male (LEP-10408) dorsal (b) and ventral (c); (d and e) female (ST ocnus) dorsal (d) and ventral (e), with specimen labels. Scale bars 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909477/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909485>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33 Deltaya ocypete comb.n. (a) male wing venation; (b and c) male (FLMNH-MGCL-209681) dorsal (b) and ventral (c); (d and e) female dorsal (d) and ventral (e). Scale bars 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909485/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909489>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34 Deltaya gen.n. representative species. (a) D. opima comb.n; (b) D. louisammour comb.n (FLMNH-MGCL-111522); (c) D. andrei comb.n; (d) D. probata comb.n. Scale bars 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909489/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909481>
    dc:description "FIGURE 31 Occulta ocnus comb.n. (a and b) male genitalia (dissection SN-19-157), lateral (a) with posterior view juxta, aedeagus lateral (b); (c–e) female genitalia (dissection NHMUK010402850), lateral view exterior tip abdomen (c), ventral view exterior tip abdomen (d), dorsal view interior abdomen (e), corpus bursae perpendicular to signa (f). Scale bars 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909481/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

